89. altaria coaptant] See above, iii. 144, and xiv. 219. ‘Quaecun- que ' is not commonly used without averb, like ‘quaevis' Itis so above, verse 56, and in the following places: iii. 156, twice in iii. 230, x. 359, xiv. 210. Here it might be taken with ‘tangunt' whatever altars they touch, but Juvenal's practice makes it probable he meant the other construction.
